Title: "The Cloud and the Pillow"

Maya lay on her bed, face pressed into the pillow, watching a single cloud drift across the sky. Her heart felt heavy, as if the whole world had turned gray. "I'm so alone," she whispered, though the words felt too big, too dramatic. She was exaggerating, she knew, but the ache in her chest made it hard to tell.

The door creaked open. Leo stood there, holding a steaming mug. "Tea?" he asked, his voice soft. "You looked like you needed it."

